    "hadith_number": "56",
    "english_translation": "Narrated by Anas bin Malik: The Prophet ﷺ said: Seven persons will be shaded by Allah under His shade on the Day when there will be no shade except His shade: A just ruler, and a youth who grew up in the worship of Allah, a man whose heart is attached to the mosque whenever he leaves until he returns to it, two men who love each other for the sake of Allah, they met upon that and parted upon that, a man who remembered Allah in solitude and his eyes flowed with tears from fear of Allah, a man whom a woman invited to commit an evil deed but he refused saying I fear Allah, the Lord of all the worlds, and a man who gave charity and hid it, so his left hand does not know what his right hand spent.",
